Listing all Linux commands along with examples would be quite extensive, as there are thousands of commands available in Linux, each with numerous options and variations. However, I can provide a list of some of the most commonly used Linux commands along with brief descriptions and examples.

Basic Commands
ls - List directory contents

bash

Verify

Open In Editor
Edit
Copy code
ls -l
